Regaud Lecture, Granada 1994. Tumors of the connective and supporting tissues. There has been a continuous acceleration of medical/scientific inquiry and of actual improvements in management of patients with neoplasms of the mesenchymal tissues over the last four decades. The number of publications in this field has increased from 1140 in 1970 and then to 1700 in 1990. Important advances discussed over this period include: establishment of sarcoma teams in major oncology centers staging systems for both soft tissue and osseous sarcomas